        "old_string": "class UpdateCacheMiddleware(MiddlewareMixin):\n    \"\"\"\n    Response-phase cache middleware that updates the cache if the response is\n    cacheable.\n\n    Must be used as part of the two-part update/fetch cache middleware.\n    UpdateCacheMiddleware must be the first piece of middleware in MIDDLEWARE\n    so that it'll get called last during the response phase.\n    \"\"\"",
        "new_string": "class UpdateCacheMiddleware(MiddlewareMixin):\n    \"\"\"\n    Response-phase cache middleware that updates the cache if the response is\n    cacheable.\n\n    This middleware caches responses based on the request URL and response headers.\n    It must be used as part of the two-part update/fetch cache middleware pattern.\n    UpdateCacheMiddleware must be the first piece of middleware in MIDDLEWARE so\n    that it'll get called last during the response phase.\n\n    The cache timeout is determined by (in order of precedence):\n    1. The page_timeout attribute (set per-instance)\n    2. The \"max-age\" value in the Cache-Control response header\n    3. The CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_SECONDS Django setting\n\n    Responses are not cached if they:\n    - Are streaming responses\n    - Have a status code other than 200 or 304\n    - Have Cache-Control directives: private, no-cache, or no-store\n    - Set user-specific cookies without request cookies\n    - Have max-age=0 in Cache-Control header\n\n    Example:\n        .. code-block:: python\n\n            MIDDLEWARE = [\n                'django.middleware.cache.UpdateCacheMiddleware',\n                # ... other middleware ...\n                'django.middleware.cache.FetchFromCacheMiddleware',\n            ]\n\n            CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_SECONDS = 600\n            CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_KEY_PREFIX = 'myapp'\n            CACHE_MIDDLEWARE_ALIAS = 'default'\n    \"\"\"",
        "replace_all": false
      },
